Name: The Wreck of the Mikko
Description: This former vessel has long since been abandoned by civilized men and mushroom alike. Now it is under the crewing of the Mouldtongues, a group of outcasts exiled for their tastings. Perhaps they would trade with you, so long as you make no mention of her.

ChildBranches.Name: Bribe the Mouldtongues for news of the latest shroomings.
ChildBranches.Description: The Mouldtongues are not of the conversable sort, but they could be bribed with a tasty morsel...

DefaultEvent.Name: A loss surely no one will miss...
DefaultEvent.Teaser: A Trade?
DefaultEvent.Description: As your crew drags the blasted thing screaming into the Bloomed Bilge, the Salivating Shipman recounts details of the lastest ongoings and misfortunate visitors. It's hard to understand him on account of the growth of fungus having eaten most of his tongue, but you make out what you can and scrimshaw a report together.

ChildBranches.Name: Offer a Docile Blemmigan for Fuel and Supplies?
ChildBranches.Description: "You have a new flavour for ussss? Yessss??

RareDefaultEvent.Name: "Yessss... We share with thosssse who share in kind."
RareDefaultEvent.Description:
The scene unfolds as you order your crew to present the blemmigan. The Salivating Shipman, with remarkable skill, quickly seizes the creature, grasping all of its tendrils in an unyielding grip. The blemmigan quivers, its fear evident in its trembling form, a primal fear only prey can truly understand.

In a rather repulsive display, the Shipman presses his moldy nose deeply into the blemmigan's cap, a sight that elicits disgust from both you and your crew. He inhales deeply, drawing in the creature's unwilling spores. For a fleeting moment, his eyes take on a swirling, peligin hue, a transformation that leaves everyone in the room consternated.

The Shipman responds, "This one believed in you, [q:Addressed as]. Makessss the flavor all the more ripe. It will not ssssuffer." His delight is evident in his voice and expression. With the blemmigan's unwilling contribution, your ship's provisions are now even more well-stocked.

DefaultEvent.Name: "Yessss... YESSSS..!"
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "I'VE WAITED WEEKSSSS FOR THISSSS..."
DefaultEvent.Description:
The horrifying scene unfolds as the man impulsively pounces on the obviously frightened blemmigan before any discussion of terms can even begin. His frenzied hands grasp the creature, and his sharp incisors tear through its cap, causing the creature to emit a disturbing fungal scream that sends shivers through your senses.

As he chews through the mushy, purple headcheese of the creature, despite its anguished protests, his peligin-scarred eyes lock onto you, and he exclaims, "It's FLAVOURRRRR! FLAVOURRRRRR! CAN YOU PUT A PRICE ON IT?!?!" The macabre spectacle leaves you and your crew with no choice but to retreat hastily to your ship. It seems the dinner bell has been sounded, you can’t bear to watch here any longer as tendrils are divided among the Mikko's crew.

The unsettling encounter has left an indelible mark on you and your crew…

ChildBranches.Name: "Donate" 40 Supplies for an Uttershroom Sporule
ChildBranches.Description:
It'll take an entire years's worth of rations, but perhaps their favour can be bought.

You can only do this once.

DefaultEvent.Name: "What'ssss that you ssssay??? A gift for the Crew?!?!?"
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "FEASSSSTING FOR DAYSSSS..."
DefaultEvent.Description:
The Salivating Shipman's tongue, tinged with purple and peligin stains, dangles from his mouth with delight. Your crew can't discern whether he's more human or zee-beast, but his unmistakable joy radiates at your generous offer. "We shall FEASSSSTH!!!" the cry goes up. The Mouldtongue's roustabouts respond with a cacophony of excitable shouts and chords that could only produced only by their fungal-choked larynxes. They eagerly load the fresh fruit and meat into the mycelium of the Bloomed Bilge. Just as you start to ponder the wastefulness of it all, The Shipman returns with a peculiar, pulsating fruit. "We took thissss from her," he says, cutting himself off and whispering, "The mushroomssss have earssss, you know. Do you undersssstand!?!?"

You don't, but nevertheless, after an uncomfortably moist handshake, you return to your ship, fleshy prize in hand, and a handkerchief in the other.

ChildBranches.Name: Propose another kind of trade
ChildBranches.Description: "Ohhhhh... I thought you'd never assssk!" This will give you lots of Supplies, but you will lose Crew and gain significant Terror.

DefaultEvent.Name: "Here. Give them this."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "A grim bargain."
DefaultEvent.Description:
"Bring ussss the bodiessss."

While the crew sleeps soundly, you invite 3 of your least loyal crew to your cabin for a toast. They gladly gulp down the bottle of chilled mushroom wine, and before they've even realized it, they are as still at the zee.

A couple of Mouldtongues assist in getting the bodies to the Bilge, and a few hours later bring crates of particularly fresh thrice-assured-as-edible fungi to the deck. Come morning, there will be questions, but they will not question the food in their bellies... or the unfortunate fertilizer used to produce it.

ChildBranches.Name: Propose another kind of trade.
ChildBranches.Description: "Ohhhhh... I thought you'd never assssk!" This will give you lots of Supplies, and you will only lose Prisoners, but you still will gain a bit of Terror.

DefaultEvent.Name: "Here. Give them thissss."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "A grim bargain."
DefaultEvent.Description:
"Bring ussss the bodiessss."

While the crew sleeps soundly, you travel down to the brig to ready the prisoners. You offer them a drink of your newly acquired vintage under the premise of guilt for their treatment while travelling. Soon, the dread of betrayal fills their eyes as the paralytic poison does it's work. You have done your part.

A couple of Mouldtongues assist in getting the bodies to the Bilge, and a few hours later bring crates of particularly fresh thrice-assured-as-edible fungi to the deck. Come morning, there will be questions, but they will not question the food in their bellies... or the unfortunate fertilizer used to produce it.

ChildBranches.Name: Ponder the doorway to the Bloomed Bilge
ChildBranches.Description: Just how deep down does the mycelium stretch?

DefaultEvent.Name: A potential adventure in the making...
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Not much here... for now...
DefaultEvent.Description: You stand before the massive bulkhead. Through the sealed porthole window you can make out a small cavern fathom that reachs deep into the wriggling mycelium below. It's hard to say, but it probably goes all the way down to the zee-floor One thing is for certain, no way to get in... At least, for now. (Under Construction Still, Coming Soon!)

ChildBranches.Name: Betray your Blemmigan Gallivanter for 333 Echoes.
ChildBranches.Description: It is considered your property under Admiralty Law after all, and the Shipman is willing to pay extra for the rich flavour of loyalty...

DefaultEvent.Name: Et' Tu Basidiocarp?
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Heartless.
DefaultEvent.Description:
You've turned your back on your trusty playful sporeling, exchanging it to be eaten alive by savages for the lust of echoes.

Quite the mycological mogul, aren't you? Well, times are tough, and a mushroom's affection doesn't pay the bills, you know. Of course, because who needs the unwavering loyalty of a fungal friend when you can have a few extra coins jingling in your pocket? Blemmigans don't put food on the table; they just provide endless companionship, endless stories, and endless growth. But who needs that?

Oh, you want to know what happened to your former friend? Think they had some grand moment of heroism with courage to spare, fighting off the festered fiends after you betrayed them like some action novel star? No. Your blemmigan is already having a grand time in the cosmogone amusement park in the roof, swapping tales of your betrayal with the other lost sporelings. "Remember that [q:Addressed as] who chose lucre over love?!" they'll say, and the ferns will weep, you're sure.

A mushroom's love is like a fine wine. It only gets better with time, unlike your financial investments, which might just disappear like spores in the wind. But hey, haven't we all traded our loyal friends to die for some pocket change at some point in our lives?

You disgust yourself, but you've acquired a small fleeting fortune. Spend it well (you won't.)

ChildBranches.Name: Demeaux Island
ChildBranches.Description: "You've been to Demeaux's Gate?"

ChildBranches.Name: Gaider's Mourn
ChildBranches.Description: "You have something to tell us about the pirate fleets of the Forest?"

ChildBranches.Name: Hunter's Keep
ChildBranches.Description: "I trust the sisters are keeping well? They are citizens of her Enduring Majesty, notionally."

ChildBranches.Name: Mt Palmerston
ChildBranches.Description: "The Brimstone Convention. They trouble me, Captain."

ChildBranches.Name: Port Cecil
ChildBranches.Description: "The Principles of Coral. I have no idea why anyone thought that settlement was a good idea."

ChildBranches.Name: Quaker's Haven
ChildBranches.Description: "Been trying the original Rubbery Lumps, have we?"

ChildBranches.Name: Venderbight
ChildBranches.Description: "What have the nearly-dead been up to, then?"

ChildBranches.Name: Whither
ChildBranches.Description: "I refuse to ask any questions. I don't want to give them the satisfaction."

DefaultEvent.Description: Out into the foggy street. Turn your collar up.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Out into the foggy street...
DefaultEvent.Name: Done

ChildBranches.Description: "You don't have anything else for us?

DefaultEvent.Description: "Hm. Apparently I'm to show you in anyway. Very well."
DefaultEvent.Name: No appointment, but -

ChildBranches.Name: Ask to speak to the Dark-Spectacled Admiral
ChildBranches.Description: "Do you have an appointment?"

DefaultEvent.Description: "Once you've proven yourself, perhaps." [Survey three ports and return, to win the Admiralty's approval.]
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Once you've proven yourself, perhaps...
DefaultEvent.Name: Not as such...

ChildBranches.Name: Ask to speak to a higher authority
ChildBranches.Description: "Do you have an appointment?"

DefaultEvent.Description: "This is - ghastly news. The poor girls. We had warned them they weren't safe, but it had been so long, I thought - well, it's done. Thank you. I will have to look into the matter of a supply post - "
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "This is - ghastly news...
DefaultEvent.Name: Open shock

ChildBranches.Name: Hunter's Keep's End
ChildBranches.Description: "I trust the sisters are keeping well? They are citizens of her Enduring Majesty, notionally."

SuccessEvent.Description: "Here is your payment. This is quite extraordinary. I must rush this upstairs immediately. One moment."
SuccessEvent.Name: "Good heavens!"

DefaultEvent.Description: "Mm. Mm. Candidly, I'm not sure why you saw fit to trouble us with this nonsense. Is there anything else?"
DefaultEvent.Name: You are met with scepticism

ChildBranches.Name: Shepherd Isles: submit as fact
ChildBranches.Description: "We do hear some peculiar tales of that place."

DefaultEvent.Description:
"This is my colleague Mr Villein, of the Ministry of Public Decency. Mr Villein, this good captain's report is here. If you would care to - yes, the fire is already lit. Let us - there we go. Now only ashes remain, and it might have caused such a lot of trouble."

"Thank you, Captain. We appreciate your discretion. Here is your payment. You need not trouble yourself further in this affair."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "This is my colleague Mr Villein, of the Ministry of Public Decency...
DefaultEvent.Name: Omitted

ChildBranches.Name: Station III
ChildBranches.Description: "Excuse me. Just let me call a colleague in - "

ChildBranches.Name: Abbey Rock
ChildBranches.Description: "We categorise it as a military installation, you know. Although that has occasioned some quite vigorous debate."

DefaultEvent.Description: "I agree: it does seem implausible. So many of the stories from that place do. Still, there is a little gold of truth in the mud of rumour, from time to time. Your payment, [q:Addressed as]".
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "I agree: it does seem implausible...
DefaultEvent.Name: Friendly scoffing

ChildBranches.Name: Shepherd Isles: submit as unsubstantiated hearsay
ChildBranches.Description: "We do hear some unlikely tales of that place."

DefaultEvent.Description: "Speak to our agent there, and return. We'll see that you're rewarded." [Visit the port below and return to London. You can check the details in your Journal at any time.]
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Speak to our agent there, and return...
DefaultEvent.Name: "This port - "

ChildBranches.Name: Ask if there's anything in particular they need

DefaultEvent.Teaser: The Admiral deals directly with more sensitive commissions...

ChildBranches.Name: Ask if there's anything in particular they need

ChildBranches.Name: The Cumaean Canal
ChildBranches.Description: "Well, if you've been there, I suppose we may as well hear about it. The fee is nominal, though."

ChildBranches.Name: Godfall
ChildBranches.Description: "Pirate-monks. I honestly have no idea what we're supposed to do about pirate-monks. What are they up to?"

DefaultEvent.Description: "Are you quite certain this is the report you wish to make? So be it."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Are you quite certain this is the report you wish to make?
DefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Pigmote Isle
ChildBranches.Description: "I'm not certain I heard you correctly."

ChildBranches.Name: Chapel of Lights
ChildBranches.Description: "There's something about the Unterzee that breeds heresy and dissent. I rather think we might need to send the Bishop of Southwark out for a good bit of Christian shouting."

ChildBranches.Name: Avid Horizon
ChildBranches.Description: "I hope you intend to tell me that everything is quiet there?"

ChildBranches.Name: Khan's Heart
ChildBranches.Description: "Been to the Salt Steppes, eh? Yes, this kind of material is always of interest. How a nation could be so barbarian and so decadent at once is beyond me. But they're terribly dangerous."

ChildBranches.Name: The Uttershroom
ChildBranches.Description: "You've spent time in Myceligaea? Dear me. I am most terribly sorry.

DefaultEvent.Description: "This is blank. Yes, both sides. No no, I assure you - no, I know, these things happen in the Republic. Consider this an ex gratia payment to cover your costs."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "This is blank...
DefaultEvent.Name: "Wait - "

RareDefaultEvent.Description: "I... no, I didn't expect that to happen. Well, perhaps it's for the best. Some reports should not be reported. No, no, don't concern yourself. This was my third-best suit, and the Admiralty offers a modest allowance for document-related damage. Perhaps it's best if you leave now, though. Good day."
RareDefaultEvent.Name: VOOOMF

ChildBranches.Name: The Iron Republic
ChildBranches.Description: "Excuse me. I need to unlock this. And this. Oops, and this. Could you place your report inside - ? Yes, I imagine someone will read it, eventually. There's always someone."

ChildBranches.Name: The Mangrove College
ChildBranches.Description: "Oh yes. The muddy philosophers. Do tell."

DefaultEvent.Description: "How curious. No spiders at all, they say? They are indeed blessed!"
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "How curious...
DefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Saviour's Rocks
ChildBranches.Description: "Goodness. We don't often hear news from there. Screaming, sometimes."

DefaultEvent.Description: "Destroyed, you say? A tragedy. My wife and I did so enjoy their silken unmentionables..."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Destroyed, you say?
DefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Saviour's Rocks
ChildBranches.Description: "Goodness. We don't often hear news from there. Screaming, sometimes."

DefaultEvent.Description: "Ye-es, well. We did rather know about his rose gardens. Not good news that they're prospering though - really should have nipped it in the, if you'll allow me, bud. Ha. And trading with the Khanate? With the Iron Republic? Bother. I may have to have a meeting about this ..."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Ye-es, well...
DefaultEvent.Name: Report Submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Isle of Cats
ChildBranches.Description: "And what does the so-called Pirate-King have to say for himself, these days?"

ChildBranches.Name: Visage
ChildBranches.Description: "Ah, the island that looks up. I don't suppose you found out what it's staring at."

ChildBranches.Name: Polythreme
ChildBranches.Description: "The King with a Hundred Hearts. What a useful fellow. Without his exports, I'd be delivering my own coal."

DefaultEvent.Description: "Such a ghastly place." A pause. "You know, there was somebody here asking about it only recently. Delightful lady, as I recall. Most delightful. Yes. I shall take the liberty of forwarding her your address..." [Something new awaits in your Lodgings]
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Such a ghastly place...
DefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Empire of Hands
ChildBranches.Description: "Oh, goodness. What are those accursed monkeys up to these days? You didn't bring any of them back with you, did you?"

DefaultEvent.Description: "I do wonder what it was that they did. Everyone says that they know, but I must confess to being curious as to what it was. Oh, well. I'm sure their lordships had reason."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "I do wonder what it was that they did...
DefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

RareDefaultEvent.Description: "Wildweald Court? When I started here, it was the Court Eternal. Then the Amaranthine Palace. Then Soulharbour. Then... I do wish they would make up their blasted minds. The filing is most annoying."
RareDefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Empire of Hands
ChildBranches.Description: "Oh, goodness. What are those accursed monkeys up to now? Don't let the Revenue Men catch you trading with them."

ChildBranches.Name: Port Carnelian
ChildBranches.Description: "You know, I sometimes wonder whether that place was a good idea. I didn't say that."

ChildBranches.Name: Nuncio
ChildBranches.Description: "Ah. Yes. The place that lures away postmen. One hears no end of complaints from the Postal Service."

ChildBranches.Name: Frostfound
ChildBranches.Description: "Is it as beautiful as they say? I doubt it. Poets are notorious liars. But liars make bad poets. A paradox, isn't it? Never mind! Your report?"

ChildBranches.Name: Aestival
ChildBranches.Description: "I had always wondered if it might be a myth - "

ChildBranches.Name: The Chelonate
ChildBranches.Description: "Is it still as revolting as they say? What about the smell?"

ChildBranches.Name: Codex
ChildBranches.Description: "Exiled for giving answers. That's Whither for you. Anything new?"

ChildBranches.Name: The Fathomking's Hold
ChildBranches.Description: "What's the old monster up to now?"

DefaultEvent.Description: The Admiralty official takes notes scrupulously, but with an expression of mild terror, like a novice vivisector wincing with a scalpel. The rest of the office studiously busy themselves with other tasks.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: The Admiralty official takes notes scrupulously, but with an expression of mild terror, like a novice vivisector wincing with a scalpel...
DefaultEvent.Name: Report submitted!

ChildBranches.Name: Grand Geode
ChildBranches.Description: "The Grand - yes. Yes, of course, we're generally quite well-informed on that topic, but since you're here, perhaps you may as well let us know what your own impressions were -"

DefaultEvent.Description: Other officials gather round to hear your tales of bloodshed and debauchery - and the jokes about the Khan that the Shadow produces so efficiently and so entertainingly. The one about the Khan and the donkey produces a roar of patriotic laughter, and encourages the Deputy Recorder to unlock the departmental drinks cabinet.

ChildBranches.Name: Kingeater's Castle
ChildBranches.Description: "Ah. Despair's fastness."

ChildBranches.Name: The Salt Lions
ChildBranches.Description: "The Bazaar has always taken an interest in that place."

ChildBranches.Description: "Mutton Island's our problem, now. I'm sure order will be restored in due course."

ChildBranches.Name: Quaker's Haven
ChildBranches.Description: "They're getting along that well, you say? Hm..."

ChildBranches.Name: Quaker's Haven
ChildBranches.Description: "We are well informed of the situation. Painfully well informed. Thank you, though."

ChildBranches.Name: Quaker's Haven

ChildBranches.Name: Quaker's Haven

ChildBranches.Name: Aigul

ChildBranches.Name: Wreck of the Mikko
ChildBranches.Description: "Not sure how anyone with a stomach could fathom tasting that giant. Just the thought of the smell alone is enough to... Ah, regardless, your fee."

SuccessEvent.Description: Sea shanties, good companionship, and the warmth of a pub fire.
SuccessEvent.Teaser: Sea shanties, good companionship, and the warmth of a pub fire...
SuccessEvent.Name: A good night out

DefaultEvent.Description: You wake in the back room of Gaston's Lampery, head pounding. You had something to drink, but beyond that it's a little hazy. Your knuckles are bloody (your blood, you think) and your shirt bloody likewise (probably not yours, unless your blood is slick and greenish). You've had better nights out. "A difficult brew," Gaston says gnomically.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: You wake in the back room of Gaston's Lampery, head pounding...
DefaultEvent.Name: A strange night out

RareSuccessEvent.Description: Sea shanties, fine food, and the warmth of a pub fire. And something more...
RareSuccessEvent.Teaser: Sea shanties, fine food, and the warmth of a pub fire...
RareSuccessEvent.Name: A marvellous night out

ChildBranches.Name: Carouse in Wolfstack Docks
ChildBranches.Description: There is no danger here. Try to enjoy yourself. [This will reduce your Terror. You might run into trouble, or romance.]

SuccessEvent.Description: Your tall tales find a ready audience. Scarred and seasoned men and women tramp aboard and find places to sling hammocks.
SuccessEvent.Teaser: Your tall tales find a ready audience...
SuccessEvent.Name: Rich pickings

DefaultEvent.Description: An eager-seeming crowd of zailors consumed all the beer you buy and then melts away. You're left with a single strabismic, melancholy seaman who wants to know if he can bring his pickled monkey aboard. "I'll pad the bottle with straw," he promises.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: An eager-seeming crowd of zailors consumed all the beer you buy and then melts away...

ChildBranches.Name: Hire on more crew
ChildBranches.Description: Sensible zailors are looking for a safe run to the tomb-colonies, or at least a sane run to the Southern Archipelago. You'll need to buy drinks, spread around hiring fees. Look for daredevils.

ChildBranches.Name: Visit your Lodgings
ChildBranches.Description: Spend some time at home.

ChildBranches.Name: Visit the Admiralty's Survey Office
ChildBranches.Description: They'll pay for information from zee-captains. Find out what, and how.

DefaultEvent.Description: "Oh yes," the University's Maritime Liaison whispers breathily. "Oh yes. This is quite a tasty one. Let me explain it to you." She (he?) explains, teeth glinting.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Oh yes," the University's Maritime Liaison whispers breathily...
DefaultEvent.Name: Quite impressed

ChildBranches.Name: Visit the University
ChildBranches.Description: The University has an inexhaustible appetite for Secrets, zee-speciments, and other tidbits of esoteric lore. Provide a Secret to prove yourself worthy of entry. [Find Secrets by locating locations of interest, or in foreign ports.]

ChildBranches.Name: Put your ship in Drydock
ChildBranches.Description: For repairs, or sometimes other purposes...

DefaultEvent.Description: It's oddly difficult to die in Fallen London; but when a Londoner is too tatty and wretched to live, they wrap themselves in bandages and take ship for the Tomb-Colonies. Your crew cart these ones aboard in padded coffins. They'll sleep there until the journey is done. [The tomb-colonist is in your hold. Take them north to the colony of Venderbight, and sell them there.]
DefaultEvent.Teaser: It's oddly difficult to die in Fallen London; but when a Londoner is too tatty and wretched to live, they wrap themselves in bandages and take ship for the Tomb-Colonies...

ChildBranches.Name: Offer passage to a Tomb-Colonist
ChildBranches.Description: An emigrant will pay to be taken north, to Venderbight.

DefaultEvent.Description: One by one, they rise, uncomplainingly, with no trace of stiffness or discomfort from the long voyage. The deck resounds beneath their heavy tread. A shroomyard manager waits on dock, tapping her foot. "About time," she says. "Here's your payment. Come along, now, you. There's a good construct."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: One by one, they rise, uncomplainingly, with no trace of stiffness or discomfort from the long voyage...
DefaultEvent.Name: Ashore

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Clay Men
ChildBranches.Description: This is where they wanted to be, or at least, where they're supposed to be.

ChildBranches.Name: A new recruit!
ChildBranches.Description: Who awaits your attention?

DefaultEvent.Description: "Sign." "Sign." "Sign." "Here's a receipt." "Here's a discretion-contract." "Here's a penalty-contract." Your vision is blurred by the end of it all. The cart rumbles off into the coiling fog. Here's your reward.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: "Sign...

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Sphinxstone
ChildBranches.Description: Special Constables - black uniforms, distinctive caps, the badge of the Ministry of Public Decency - wait with a cart.

DefaultEvent.Description: Your blemmigan leaps from the rail of the ship to shelter in the stranger's greatcoat, and the stranger nods unsteadily. "We'll see to it," the fluting voice assures you. It places a box atop a quayside bollard - clumsily, its hand muffled in its sleeve. Then it's gone, leaving only an odour of marsh-mud lingering in the air. What's in the box?
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Your blemmigan leaps from the rail of the ship to shelter in the stranger's greatcoat, and the stranger nods unsteadily...
DefaultEvent.Name: Welcome, blemmigan

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver a Blemmigan
ChildBranches.Description: A greatcoat-clad figure waits in the shadow of a crane. "You have blemmigans?" it enquires hopefully. Its voice is high, fluting. A scarf conceals its face.

DefaultEvent.Description: Your blemmigans swirl across the dock like clawed and violet fog. Up into the greatcoat, like squirrels into a shrub! "Thank you all," the figure flutes. "We have something for you - and we wanted you to have this, our work. Though it's unsigned, of course." It retreats into the dockside mist, leaving behind a dank odour; a packing-crate; and some love poetry...
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Your blemmigans swirl across the dock like clawed and violet fog...
DefaultEvent.Name: Welcome, blemmigans!

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Blemmigans
ChildBranches.Description: A greatcoat-clad figure waits in the shadow of a crane. "You have blemmigans?" it enquires hopefully. Its voice is high, fluting. A scarf conceals its face.

DefaultEvent.Description:
A black carriage - stripped of livery - slows beside you. When the door opens, a veiled woman in midnight-blue gestures curtly. "In," she demands. 

You wait on a deep-cushioned seat. A furrow-browed old gentleman with a mild and sheeply gaze samples the honey. He nods approvingly. The upholstery smells like flowers and rust.

"Go," the veiled woman says. She tosses you a lacquered serpent-bracelet. It's freezing to the touch. Its mouth is stuffed with jewels.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: A black carriage - stripped of livery - slows beside you...
DefaultEvent.Name: The Veiled Lady

RareDefaultEvent.Description:
A clatter of hooves; hoarse voices raised in song. A phaeton pulls up beside you, slewing dangerously. Two bandaged figures sit hunched at the front. "Honey!" one croaks. "Quickly!"

You pass up the barrel, and they heft it as if it were empty. "I'm a terrible person," she tells you dolefully. "But so are you. And it tastes so sweet. Here's your money."

And they're off! with a cackle, a blown kiss, and a waft of cigar-smoke.
RareDefaultEvent.Teaser: A clatter of hooves; hoarse voices raised in song...
RareDefaultEvent.Name: An encounter with the Mercies

ChildBranches.Name: Honey at the crossroads
ChildBranches.Description: "Wait here," the instructions said. "Wear a crimson feather in your hat."

SuccessEvent.Description: Sea shanties, fine food, and the warmth of a pub fire. And something more...
SuccessEvent.Teaser: Sea shanties, fine food, and the warmth of a pub fire...
SuccessEvent.Name: A marvellous night out

DefaultEvent.Description: You wake in the back room of Gaston's Lampery, head pounding. You had something to drink, but beyond that it's a little hazy. Your knuckles are bloody (your blood, you think) and your shirt bloody likewise (probably not yours, unless your blood is slick and greenish). You've had better nights out. "A difficult brew," Gaston says gnomically.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: You wake in the back room of Gaston's Lampery, head pounding...
DefaultEvent.Name: A strange night out

RareSuccessEvent.Description: Sea shanties, fine food, and the warmth of a pub fire. And something more...
RareSuccessEvent.Teaser: Sea shanties, fine food, and the warmth of a pub fire...
RareSuccessEvent.Name: A marvellous night out

ChildBranches.Name: Carouse in Wolfstack Docks
ChildBranches.Description: There is no danger here. Try to enjoy yourself. [This will reduce your Terror. You might run into trouble, or romance.]

SuccessEvent.Description: Sea shanties, good companionship, and the warmth of a pub fire.
SuccessEvent.Teaser: Sea shanties, good companionship, and the warmth of a pub fire...
SuccessEvent.Name: A good night out

ChildBranches.Name: Carouse in Wolfstack Docks
ChildBranches.Description: There is no danger here. Try to enjoy yourself. [This will reduce your Terror. You might run into trouble, or romance.]

DefaultEvent.Description: Her skin glows with health. Her smile is wise and merciless.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Her skin glows with health...
DefaultEvent.Name: Bright gown, bright hair

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Sphinxstone to... ?
ChildBranches.Description: A smiling woman in an elegant jonquil gown places a gloved hand on your arm. "Are you waiting for the Ministry men? They won't be coming. But I have a proposition for you."

DefaultEvent.Description: He stoops like a clerk and coughs like a miner. But that frock-coat is of the finest fabric and the newest cut. "My name is Penstock," he says.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: He stoops like a clerk and coughs like a miner...
DefaultEvent.Name: Tired eyes, sallow skin

ChildBranches.Name: A dusty gentleman
ChildBranches.Description: "Captain! Wait! She gave you an errand, didn't she? She serves a certain Power - a bright one, but not a friendly one. I have a counter-proposal. Will you listen?"

DefaultEvent.Description: He stoops like a clerk and coughs like a miner. But that frock-coat is of the finest fabric and the newest cut. "My name is Penstock," he says.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: He stoops like a clerk and coughs like a miner...
DefaultEvent.Name: Tired eyes, sallow skin

ChildBranches.Name: A dusty gentleman
ChildBranches.Description: "Captain! A moment. You turned her down, didn't you? That was wise. The Power she serves is no friend to London, or to the Bazaar. I have a proposal of my own. Will you listen?"

DefaultEvent.Description:
You still have contacts in the urchin-gangs; you still have favours owed. Your skills and alliances and your knowledge of the Flit-ways is enough to get the stone up, though your zailors are green with terror by the end of it. "I want to go back to zee, captain!" one moans.

The urchin Slivvy has arranged cradles for the rocks. "We are going to drop them on people Storm doesn't like," he tells you. "Squash them f-f-flat. It's all right if a g-g-god tells you to do it." Is he joking? It's difficult to tell, with Slivvy. He leans forward and whispers the directions to the Backmost Stairs, the secret Flit-route that you've never travelled.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: You still have contacts in the urchin-gangs; you still have favours owed...
DefaultEvent.Name: Step by step

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Sphinxstone to the boy Slivvy
ChildBranches.Description: Slivvy is the fey and stuttering shaman-boy who speaks to the wind. Slivvy lives in the Flit, the rooftop kingdom of Fallen London, where urchins and anarchists lair. It's not far. But it is high. It won't be easy to get the Sphinxstone up there.

DefaultEvent.Description: That night, you wait behind the vestry with a rented wagon full of stones. You've sent your zailors back to the ship. Your successor is prompt. He seems disinclined to look you in the eye. "We have instructions," he says quietly. "We require an altar, and we must use one of these - objects." He does look up, then. "Why? Who are you working for now? Does the Bazaar rule the Church? I don't understand. But they told me to give you this, and these." 'These' are your old vestments... and a Bible. POST-FINAL REVISED EXCEPTIONAL EDITION. All holy books have been amended since London fell, modified by St Cyriac's College and the Ministry of Public Decency. This one contains certain special amendments.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: That night, you wait behind the vestry with a rented wagon full of stones...
DefaultEvent.Name: Crimes past

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Sphinxstone to your successor in your old parish church
ChildBranches.Description: Why? You can't face the man. But you must, if you wish to fulfil Penstock's commission.

DefaultEvent.Description:
The Shrine moves constantly, but you have directions from Penstock. Tonight, it is here, at the bottom of a narrow flight of stairs that leads down to the Stolen River, that you find the shrine. It is hung with irrigo. Its altar is a stool, with the icon of St Joshua set upon it. You shield your eyes against the sapping colour. Already you've forgotten the route you took to come here. With luck, the zailors waiting above with the stone will not have wandered off.

"The Salt Lions," the Midnighter says breathily. "Oh yes, oh yes. That must be forgotten. Don't worry: we'll purge the stone of what remains. We're grateful to you, although you won't remember why - "

And now here you are behind the warehouses at the docks. Your hands and lips are cold. Here, in your pocket, is a tattered book.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: The Shrine moves constantly, but you have directions from Penstock...
DefaultEvent.Name: The Shrine of St Joshua

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Sphinxstone for Penstock
ChildBranches.Description: St Joshua is the patron saint of spies and intriguers. His clergy are the Midnighters: steeped in secrets and wrapped in irrigo. Penstock wishes you to take the Sphinxstone to them.

ChildBranches.Name: Decide whether to complete the Avuncular Broker's mission
ChildBranches.Description: The Hands-On Diplomat is anxious to take up her new post. "And no doubt you're anxious to be paid."

DefaultEvent.Description: She hisses with delight as she examines what you've brought. "Yes. Yes, this brings the Day much closer. Here. We won't insult you with payment, but we've brought supplies to defray your costs. And these souls. They are our gratitude: they were donated, freely. Do what you will with them."
DefaultEvent.Teaser: She hisses with delight as she examines what you've brought...
DefaultEvent.Name: "O wonderful - "

ChildBranches.Name: Deliver Supplies for the Work
ChildBranches.Description: A Burning-Eyed Student waits at the abandoned lime-kilns by Watchmaker's Hill.

DefaultEvent.Description: He goes ashore with his fish-skin knapsack, his shark-skin boots, the little wash-leather bag that the bo'sun gave him to carry his tools. He sets up shop in a shack behind the Blind Helmsman. Over the months, curiosity brings visitors to see the bone-carving savage from the rotting shell-city. His skill is significant; his reputation, more so. He learns to trade on it. When last you see his name, it's on a Mahogany Hall hand-bill, as the Bone-Chronicler who tells fortunes on stage.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: He goes ashore with his fish-skin knapsack, his shark-skin boots, the little wash-leather bag that the bo'sun gave him to carry his tools...
DefaultEvent.Name: A modest reputation

ChildBranches.Name: Release the Scrimshaw Chronicler from your service
ChildBranches.Description: He's considering staying in London. "I could open a shop," he says, "by the docks. There's bone here, too. There's always bone."

ChildBranches.Name: Drinks with the Cheery Man
ChildBranches.Description: You have an open invitation to the Medusa's Head.

ChildBranches.Name: Visit the Rose-Market
ChildBranches.Description: It bustles on Roser's Wharf. Perhaps you can find a buyer for some of the curiosities you've found at zee.

DefaultEvent.Description:
You extend your hand and the Blemmigan leaps on. Its tendrils entwine with your fingers, and it chitters quietly. It meets your gaze and bobs its dome in greeting. It's very small – is it old enough for naval service? You're pretty sure its moustache has been drawn on in pen, in an attempt to look older.

As you approach your ship's gangplank, the creature flutes and vibrates with apparent happiness. The bosun winces as you bring it aboard.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: You extend your hand and the Blemmigan leaps on...
DefaultEvent.Name: A polite bow

ChildBranches.Name: Adopt a Blemmigan Gallivanter
ChildBranches.Description: A Blemmigan sits atop a splintered crate, clicking and whistling at captains as they come near.

DefaultEvent.Description:
The sticker on the window says CLOSING SALE! ALL DOGS MUST FIND A HOME! Behind the sign, another sign bleeds through, it’s harder to read since the newer letters block out a good chunk of underlying letters (seemingly on purpose) but squinting at it, it looks something like: C H E L P O S L I N G O S A L E! L A L L O Z E E D O C A P T A I N S M U S T W A N T E D! H O M E! N E E D E D!

You enter the lobby…
DefaultEvent.Teaser: The sticker on the window says CLOSING SALE!..
DefaultEvent.Name: Time to puruse the puppies!

ChildBranches.Name: Visit the local adoption center for the first time.
ChildBranches.Description: Adopting a pet is a large responsibility.

DefaultEvent.Description: The half-rubbery clerk greets you with a cheery smile. "Welcome back!" Time to puruse the puppies!
DefaultEvent.Teaser: The half-rubbery clerk...
DefaultEvent.Name: The sounds of hounds clamour from within.

ChildBranches.Name: Visit the local adoption center: Mr. Marley's Mutt Mission.
ChildBranches.Description: Adopting a pet is a large responsibility.

Description: She's the greatest city on the Unterzee. And don't you forget it.
Teaser: She's the greatest city on the Unterzee...
Name: London!
A small stately rubbery man? He sits at a desk...
Teaser: A small stately rubbery man? He sits at a desk......
Description: As you look through the glass, a rubbery figure attends to a dog at their desk.

ChildBranches.Name: Enter the adoption center.
ChildBranches.Description: What companions shall we find inside?

DefaultEvent.Name: Oh wait! Excuse you.
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Oh wait! Excuse you...
DefaultEvent.Description: A ~half~ rubbery woman! She sits at a desk inside of a large boarding house designed for dogs of various sizes. Her head is a mix of tentacles and hair with a white rubbery pearl head. She has her eyes (and her other eyes) focused on feeding a rather guarded Pointer, who immediately reveals your trespass as a potential customer to the establishment. You think to yourself that at some point or another, this place had to have been filled with mounds of mutts of all kinds, but now only a small handful appear unadopted. The half-rubbery woman has approached you. "Hello! Welcome to Mr. Marley’s Mutt Mission! Would you like to meet our furry friends we have left? They make for remarkable companions you know? Would you like a labrador? He keeps stealing the treats and holding them for ransom, so you’ll need to be careful with his food, but he needs a good home…" She leans over and gesturing with a tentacle- she whispers, "Honestly, we can’t afford to keep paying him."

Name: "Hey, wanna snag the most adorable pup ever?"
Description:
"Right this please way, and do watch your step." She leads you down a long hallway filled with cages of all kinds before you enter a large play room designed for greeting the dogs. The room is filled with puppies of all sorts.

You can take one home with you, if you can pay the adoption fee.

ChildBranches.Name: Adopt a Larcenous Labrador.
ChildBranches.Description: "Absolutely no joke, Mr. Marley is urging us to find a new home for our furry friend, and you are welcome to take him at no cost. But be ready, once he's in your care, managing his antics becomes your responsibility."

DefaultEvent.Name: Swashbarkler On Board!
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Welcome to the crew
DefaultEvent.Description: "Mr. Marley's dead set on it – the pup's all yours if you're up for it. His last owner called him Cap'n Salty because he's crazy about salted crackers. It's smart to have a stash on hand, you know, just in case he gets the itch for some plundering. Take some with you, and by the way, he's a top-notch fighter." No sooner than you accept the box, your newly adopted canine companion comes bounding around the corner; he wears a black corsair’s coat and a black pirate’s hat to match, with fur as golden as the sun. As he runs to you, you've realized all too late that he has no intention of stopping! AVAST! The fiend has taken you to the ground and has your throat by the blade he’s unsheathed with his mouth. He holds the sword to your neck. He is not upset however, quite the opposite, he seems rather proud of himself and it seems he is expecting you to be as well. He eyes the box in your hand and gestures for the whole thing? REALLY? A whole box of crackers for a mutt? Fat chance. He presses the blade further in, just enough to remind you he is not negotiating... Alright, just this one time... You surrender your bounty of salted crackers, and Salty lets you off the ground, content with his plunder. "Come on now [q:Addressed as], he’s just a dog. You’ll have to do better than that if you want him to believe you’re his master and not the other way around, but I am sure you’ll get the hang of it eventually." She giggles to herself.

ChildBranches.Name: Adopt a Boilermaker Beagle.
ChildBranches.Description: \He'd be a brilliant employee, no doubt! He's a proper talented pooch. Managed to wrangle in a massive bonfire for his gotcha day – it's part of the deal for him working here, you know? But we're a bit short on resources. Could you lend us a hand to make his release go smoothly?"

DefaultEvent.Name: A Timid Start...
DefaultEvent.Teaser: Welcome to the crew.
DefaultEvent.Description:
"Got it sorted, eh? Brilliant! Follow me to the playground. Get your crew to drop off the coal there, and I'll go fetch Mr. Marley pronto. He's got a telegram to send to the fire station; we're creating a fair bit of smoke, and we wouldn't want them getting the wrong idea, now would we?"

After a few 'short' trips from the ship, everyone has gathered around, and at this point, a small crowd of onlookers as well. "Well, lets get bl___dy on with it then!" cries Marley- the order to begin!

As the way is cleared for the inferno to start, you spot your soon to be adopted beagle amidst the chaos, he's returned your gaze with an uncertain glance from behind the Clerk's legs. He wears a custom-tailored engineers outfit, layered and caked with dog-years of oilstains and grunge. Fresh gunk gleams along his vest, indicative he was in some dirty pipe work when you arrived, and no time for a wash either. You wonder how it's even possible to spill that much oil on yourself.

Initially wary and distant, the weathered canine hesitated. Yet, as the bonfire began to roar, that subtle trance crept in. The flickering flames danced a raging warmth, and the dog's once guarded eyes sparked. Drawn out gradatim by the vapid crimsons and coronas of the flame, he cautiously approached, and together, with you, in the glow of that bonfire, a connection was forged. The shared duet among the dancing flames bridged the gap in his heart. Your crew dances the night away while the Terrior performs; A fitting piece to revel with as coal and wood become ash... the night has concluded, and for the Beagle, he's made up his mind.

He’s ready for his first assignment.
